Description.value:
This is a template for scenario-specific inbound conversion flows that you can copy and adapt to your needs:
- Configure a unique ProcessDirect endpoint of the flow.
- Add flow steps to transform the incoming message, e.g., JSON to XML, CSV to XML, unzip, decoder, scripts, etc.
- If you like to define customer specific header properties in the inbound conversion flow instead of the inbound processing flow to be able to search message logs based on payload data, first define exchange properties by parsing the XML message (assuming that the converted message body is in XML format), then maintain name/value pairs in the header customHeaderProperties following the pattern: prop1:${property.prop1}|prop2:${property.prop2}.
- In case of multiple Service Interface Operations, maintain mapping between Operation and Message Type if not already done in the scenario-specific inbound processing flow. If required here, apply the following naming convention: For each operation create exchange property with name SAP-MT2OP-<Operation name> and value <Message Type name>.
- Otherwise, delete flow steps that you do not need.
- Maintain exception handling to your needs.
For more details, please refer to the documentation (see link in Documents section of the package).
